				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok i've recently gotten by bard alt up to the level where i'm thinking about going to Iceclad as so many have done and practice Kiting.
<br />

<br />
I understand the basic components of Kiting fine, however I want to know what features of PBAE kiting were nerfed. I assume since I have not played a bard before that the range on the early damage spells is seriously nerfed, specifically CoD and DDD. 
<br />

<br />
I get land messages on mobs now when i practice kiting a single around, but I never get damage messages. I assume this is in a nutshell how they nerfed AE kiting. Am I correct in this assumption?
<br />

<br />
If in fact such massive kites were nerfed? What does everyone do now 27-35ish for lots of exp. 
<br />

<br />
Are we bards limited to Charm Soloing (Bards seem to call it swarm kiting) and Fear Kites?
<br />

<br />
Sorry if my question is typically noob. I've read all the guides, but I was worried about information in those guides being outdated by the EverPatch team at sony.
<br />

<br />
Game on
<br />

<br />
Lewellen Loquacious</span></td>
