				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: To what extent was Point Blank AE Kiting Nerfed?<a name="71221"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 17 04 5:30 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Are we bards limited to Charm Soloing (Bards seem to call it swarm kiting) and Fear Kites?</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
We call it something different becaues it is. Charm kiting is making a pet and sending it against a target while helping your pet kill the target. Swarm kiting is charming a pet and sending it against a group (or swarm) of other mobs, allowing them to beat it into the dirt. Just before it dies, you break the charm and kill the former pet yourself. This allows for a much higher kill rate. Also, you get 100% of the experience for the kill, vs the inverse percentage of experience you get for a charmed pet assisting in a kill.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
